{"title":"To Tu Fu From Shantung","author":{"name":"Li Po"},"publishDate":"2005-10-26","lines":[{"line":"You ask how I spend my time–","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"I nestle against a treetrunk","stanza":1,"number":2},{"line":"and listen to autumn winds","stanza":1,"number":3},{"line":"in the pines all night and day.","stanza":1,"number":4},{"line":"Shantung wine can’t get me drunk.","stanza":2,"number":5},{"line":"The local poets bore me.","stanza":2,"number":6},{"line":"My thoughts remain with you,","stanza":2,"number":7},{"line":"like the Wen River, endlessly flowing.","stanza":2,"number":8}]}